bago-ED wrote: <br>
<br>
[Quote: The assisted person does not need to have auto-attack on for /assist to work. <br>
<br>
Does this mean that if I am main assist and I am targeting a mob, anyone who assists me automatically attacks that mob? If so this will be a big problem. There are many times that I have a mob targeted but I do not want to attack it (i.e. taunting messed mobs, waiting for chanter to mes one before attacking other, checking what mobs are there and their health before choosing, etc.). I don't think assist should work until the person who is being assisted actually attacks. There will be big problems otherwise. ]<br>
<br>
Yes, this is how it works by default. If you /assist someone, their target becomes your target and you begin to auto-attack. <br>
<br>
If you don't want to have auto-attack start when you use /assist, you can turn that off in your eqclient.ini file. Just open the file with a text editor and change this line: <br>
<br>
AttackOnAssist=TRUE <br>
<br>
To read: <br>
<br>
AttackOnAssist=FALSE <br>
<br>
Do this and /assist will not turn on auto-attack.<br>
<br>
<br>
Ok, I would suggest that everyone go into their EQclient.ini file and change this to not attack when using assist <br>
